Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.77,0:02:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.01,0:02:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a historic moment! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.41,0:02:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Our studio has moved \Nand is now located only minutes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.68,0:02:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,from the new world headquarters complex \Nat Warwick, New York.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.02,0:02:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And this first program \Nfrom our new studio \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.15,0:02:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,will bring you \Nmany spiritual gems.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.02,0:02:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,First, what obstacles \Nhave been overcome \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.33,0:02:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so that common people \Ncan read God’s Word? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.43,0:02:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In this exciting documentary, \Nwe will see the courage shown \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.97,0:02:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by William Tyndale of England.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.40,0:02:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped two fierce enemies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.84,0:02:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to become close friends? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.74,0:02:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The uniting power \Nof the Bible is evident \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.64,0:02:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in this account. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.68,0:02:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And what can we learn \Nfrom the apostle Paul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.75,0:02:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that will improve our ministry? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.55,0:02:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We will find out as we join this family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.65,0:02:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,during their Family Worship evening. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.36,0:02:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the January program \Nof JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.55,0:03:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,As Jehovah’s Witnesses, \Nwe truly love the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.05,0:03:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we know it is God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.95,0:03:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why we love reading it, \Nwe love studying it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.76,0:03:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and we love learning about its history. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.73,0:03:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When we pause \Nfor a moment and reflect on \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.03,0:03:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the many efforts that have been made \Nthrough the centuries \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.40,0:03:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to hinder and even stop \Nthe distribution of the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.81,0:03:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes obvious \Nthat its Author, Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.48,0:03:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,has been personally involved \Nin preserving \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.85,0:03:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and making known \Nhis precious Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.88,0:03:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very much \Nin harmony with the thought \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.89,0:04:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in Isaiah 40:8: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.36,0:04:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“The green grass dries up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.43,0:04:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“the blossom withers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.96,0:04:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but the word\Nof our God endures forever.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.20,0:04:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,With that in mind, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.97,0:04:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m happy to speak \Nwith you this month \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.31,0:04:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,on a theme \Nthat’s very close to my heart:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.88,0:04:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Word of Our God Endures Forever.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.88,0:04:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The more we come to appreciate \Nthe value of God’s Word, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.45,0:04:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the more we’ll be moved to read it\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.09,0:04:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and, even more important, \Nto apply it in our lives.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.53,0:04:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave us an outstanding gift \Nwhen he inspired \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.66,0:04:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,faithful men \Nto record his precious Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.67,0:04:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s through the pages of God’s Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.64,0:04:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that we learn \Njust how much God loves us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.04,0:04:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, his Word contains \Nguidance on how to live. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.74,0:04:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It outlines his purpose \Nin creating us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.65,0:05:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives us his precious promises \Nfor life everlasting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.02,0:05:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in peace and happiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.46,0:05:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder the apostle Paul \Nwas inspired to write \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.19,0:05:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,at 2 Timothy 3:16, 17: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.83,0:05:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“All Scripture is inspired of God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“and beneficial for teaching, \Nfor reproving, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.51,0:05:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“for setting things straight, \Nfor disciplining in righteousness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.44,0:05:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that the man of God \Nmay be fully competent, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.25,0:05:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,completely equipped for every good work.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.69,0:05:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, Satan the Devil \Ndoes not want people to have access \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.92,0:05:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to these precious truths \Nfrom our heavenly Father, Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.09,0:05:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s no surprise \Nthat there have been many obstacles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.87,0:05:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to making the Bible available. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.17,0:05:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,While Satan may not have been \Ndirectly behind all of these, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.04,0:05:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,he certainly \Nhas made use of them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.61,0:06:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What are some \Nof these obstacles, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.11,0:06:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and how have they been overcome?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.81,0:06:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider the first obstacle: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.75,0:06:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,language barriers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.45,0:06:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The first 39 books of the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.09,0:06:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,which are often called the Old Testament, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.86,0:06:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,were written primarily \Nin the Hebrew language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.56,0:06:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,These books were known \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.86,0:06:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,by Hebrew-speaking servants of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.20,0:06:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,However, as time went on,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.00,0:06:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,particularly after \Nthe destruction of Babylon, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.27,0:06:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,many Jews established communities \Nin other nations of the earth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.68,0:06:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of these Jews spoke Greek. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.55,0:06:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They no longer used Hebrew. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.08,0:06:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That meant that many Jews \Nno longer had access \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.95,0:06:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Scriptures in a language \Nthey could understand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.66,0:06:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider what had happened. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.13,0:06:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As Alexander the Great conquered \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.36,0:06:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,more and more \Nof the then-known world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.80,0:06:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Greek gradually became \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:06:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the common language \Nof commerce and government \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.97,0:07:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout his empire. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.14,0:07:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If the Bible \Nwas to be understood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,by the Jews and by Jewish proselytes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.84,0:07:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,who were scattered throughout \Nthis vast Greek-speaking territory, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.08,0:07:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it needed to be translated into Greek. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.22,0:07:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Beginning in about the year 250 B.C.E., \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.36,0:07:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the Hebrew Scriptures began \Nto be translated into Greek. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.59,0:07:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, that Greek translation \Ncame to be known \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.76,0:07:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,as the Septuagint. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.90,0:07:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It was widely and frequently used \Nby the Christians \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.60,0:07:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in the first century who spoke Greek. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.41,0:07:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the writers \Nof the Christian Greek Scriptures,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.68,0:07:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which is often called \Nthe New Testament, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.35,0:07:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,frequently quoted directly \Nfrom that translation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.32,0:07:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So that obstacle had been overcome. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.32,0:07:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But there were many more \Nlanguage obstacles ahead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.49,0:08:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As the Roman Empire \Nbegan to flourish, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.06,0:08:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Latin replaced Greek \Nas a common language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.47,0:08:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it was necessary \Nto translate the Bible into Latin. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.94,0:08:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Some Latin translations \Nof the Bible books began to appear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.44,0:08:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was in the year 405 C.E. \Nthat Jerome completed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.38,0:08:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the definitive Latin translation \Nof the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.02,0:08:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It came to be known \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.22,0:08:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as the Latin Vulgate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.22,0:08:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerome’s translation \Nwould become \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.29,0:08:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the standard Bible \Nused by Christendom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.33,0:08:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,for the next nearly 1,000 years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.10,0:08:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Latin soon became \Nthe language of the learned and the elite, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.00,0:08:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,so the common people \Ncould no longer understand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.74,0:08:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible’s message.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.91,0:08:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,During that long period, \Nthere were sincere men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.78,0:08:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that translated portions of the Bible \Ninto some additional languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.02,0:09:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but these translations were, \Nof course, all made by hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.63,0:09:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Such handwritten copies of the Bible \Nwere rare and expensive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.60,0:09:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, \Naccess to the Bible in vernacular, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.07,0:09:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,or common languages, \N was very limited.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.74,0:09:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But language was not \Nthe only obstacle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.84,0:09:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that threatened to prevent \Nthe distribution of God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.34,0:09:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider a second factor: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.35,0:09:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,direct opposition \Nto Bible translation and distribution \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.99,0:09:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,from religious leaders.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.52,0:09:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That opposition \Nstarted to increase in 1229 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.49,0:09:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when the local church \NCouncil of Toulouse decreed:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.96,0:09:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,, “We prohibit also \Nthat the laity should be permitted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.33,0:09:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to have the books \Nof the Old or the New Testament.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.34,0:09:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1234, \Nthe Council of Tarragona decreed: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.04,0:09:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“No one should possess the books \Nof the Old or the New Testament \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.78,0:10:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the vernacular [language], \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.98,0:10:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“and if anyone possesses them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.12,0:10:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“let him deliver them, within eight days \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.72,0:10:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“from the promulgation of this decree, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.49,0:10:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to the local bishop, \Nso that they may be burned.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.03,0:10:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, during \Na very long period in history, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.60,0:10:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,there was limited access to the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.51,0:10:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in the languages \Nspoken by common people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.74,0:10:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But did that mean \Nthat the Word of God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.74,0:10:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,would not continue to endure?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.31,0:10:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither language barriers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.68,0:10:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,nor opposition from religious leaders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.29,0:10:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,could stop God’s Word \Nfrom being made known. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.32,0:10:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in those dark times, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.89,0:10:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,there were individuals \Nwho loved God’s Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.03,0:10:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and who worked hard \Nto translate it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.76,0:10:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and to make it available to others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.80,0:10:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider John Wycliffe \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.80,0:10:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and his followers \Nwho were called the Lollards.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:10:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,John Wycliffe and his associates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.68,0:11:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,completed the translation \Nof the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.81,0:11:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,into English \Nabout the year 1382. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.02,0:11:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They eagerly \Nhand copied the translation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.52,0:11:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and then traveled \Nfrom village to village \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.99,0:11:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,reading the Bible \Nto the common people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.39,0:11:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite tremendous opposition \Nfrom the church, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.93,0:11:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Wycliffe and his followers \Nmade the Bible available \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.83,0:11:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to many honesthearted people \Nin the English language.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.44,0:11:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,After Wycliffe died in 1384, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.81,0:11:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,great opposition \Ncame to his followers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Many had land \Nand property confiscated. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.41,0:11:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Others were burned \Nat the stake.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.72,0:11:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In response to the work \Nof Wycliffe and the Lollards, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1408, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.52,0:11:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Arundel, \NArchbishop of Canterbury, declared: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.76,0:11:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“We therefore decree and ordain \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.83,0:12:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“that no man shall, hereafter, \Nby his own authority, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.77,0:12:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“translate any text of the Scripture \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.84,0:12:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“into English, \Nor any other tongue, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.94,0:12:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . upon pain \Nof greater excommunication.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.92,0:12:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Did such opposition \Nwipe out efforts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.95,0:12:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to translate and make \Nthe Bible available? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.19,0:12:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The work of Wycliffe \Nand his associates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.56,0:12:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,stimulated interest in the Bible \Nthroughout England \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.96,0:12:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and even as far as central Europe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.57,0:12:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Religious leaders were not able \Nto silence the Word of God.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.57,0:12:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, within just a few decades \Nafter Wycliffe’s death, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.51,0:12:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,two factors \Nled to a tremendous increase \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.25,0:12:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in the availability \Nof the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.19,0:12:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The first, \Nabout the year 1454, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.82,0:12:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,was the development \Nof printing with movable type. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.06,0:13:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This invention would \Nin time allow for the printing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.23,0:13:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of large quantities \Nof Bibles in many languages.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.04,0:13:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The second factor was \Nthe compiling and printing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.97,0:13:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Hebrew and Greek \Noriginal language text \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.88,0:13:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Holy Scriptures. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.88,0:13:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This allowed many translators \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.32,0:13:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to have access \Nto the original language texts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.85,0:13:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they then could produce \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.99,0:13:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,high-quality translations \Nin their own languages.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.19,0:13:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the result? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.33,0:13:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 1500’s across Europe, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.00,0:13:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,fresh translations \Nwere made and printed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.47,0:13:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in vernacular, \Nor common languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.00,0:13:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,including German, English, Italian, French, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.21,0:13:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Dutch, Czech, Danish, Swedish, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.01,0:13:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Spanish, Slovenian, and many others.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.88,0:13:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,However, opposition continued. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.75,0:14:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible translators were frequently hounded \Nby the Inquisition, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.46,0:14:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and some translators like \NWilliam Tyndale and John Rogers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.16,0:14:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,were even put to death \Nfor their work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.30,0:14:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, the Word of God \Ncontinued to endure \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.64,0:14:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and be made available \Nto more and more language groups.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.27,0:14:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,By the early 1800’s, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.01,0:14:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible translation \Nbegan to speed up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.15,0:14:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible societies \Nand intrepid translators \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.72,0:14:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,began to work \Nin many parts of the earth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.79,0:14:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the Bible began \Nto appear in languages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.96,0:14:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of Asia, Africa, \Nthe Pacific islands, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.76,0:14:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as in indigenous languages \Nof the Americas. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.90,0:14:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,From 1800 to 1899, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.77,0:14:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,some portions of the Bible \Nwere translated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.67,0:14:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,into some 400 languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.64,0:14:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and from 1900 to 1950, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.48,0:14:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 500 languages \Nwere added.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.98,0:15:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider what has been accomplished \Nwith the New World Translation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.82,0:15:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As of this month, \Nthe New World Translation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.36,0:15:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,has been produced \Nin whole or in part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.53,0:15:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in 149 languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.73,0:15:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,with an additional \N37 languages approved.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.77,0:15:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s obvious \Nthat neither language barriers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.77,0:15:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,nor opposition \Nfrom religious leaders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.67,0:15:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was able to stop \Nthe distribution of God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.48,0:15:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has protected it \Nthrough the ages. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.98,0:15:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just as Psalm 12:6, 7 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.32,0:15:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“The sayings of Jehovah are pure; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.09,0:15:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“they are like silver refined \Nin an earthen furnace, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.96,0:15:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“purified seven times. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.86,0:15:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will guard them, O Jehovah; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.73,0:15:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“you will protect each one of them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.20,0:15:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,from this generation forever.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.61,0:16:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jehovah \Nhas protected each one \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.71,0:16:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of his precious sayings \Ndown through the ages.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.32,0:16:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But consider a third obstacle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.82,0:16:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Although the Bible is now available \Nin whole or in part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.99,0:16:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in almost 3,000 languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.13,0:16:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,many people are no longer interested \Nin reading it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.70,0:16:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In our modern age, \Npeople have become\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.20,0:16:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,increasingly skeptical and irreligious. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.24,0:16:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Scientists have extolled \Nthe theory of evolution \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.54,0:16:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and have made it appear intelligent \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.91,0:16:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to doubt the existence of God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.51,0:16:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.51,0:16:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,secular philosophy has encouraged people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.18,0:16:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to make life decisions \Naccording to what feels right to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.52,0:16:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the result? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A world where people \Nare often guided \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.53,0:16:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,by their own selfish, fleshly desires. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.36,0:16:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of leading to happiness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.60,0:17:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,many people are left \Nfeeling empty and dissatisfied.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.07,0:17:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How is this third obstacle overcome? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.34,0:17:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Around the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.24,0:17:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,people are opening \NGod’s Word, the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.71,0:17:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and reading it \Nfor themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.95,0:17:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re recognizing \Nthat its thoughts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.05,0:17:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,are not simply human wisdom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.35,0:17:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,As they apply \Nits principles in their lives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.09,0:17:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,they find \Ncontentment and joy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.73,0:17:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They develop \Nself-respect and dignity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.56,0:17:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from living according to \Nthe upright moral standards \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.10,0:17:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,outlined by our Creator. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.37,0:17:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As Psalm 119:97-100 states: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.88,0:17:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“How I do love your law! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.48,0:17:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“I ponder over it all day long. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your commandment \Nmakes me wiser than my enemies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.99,0:17:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“because it is with me forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.59,0:17:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have more insight \Nthan all my teachers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.09,0:17:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“because I ponder over your reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.33,0:18:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“I act with more understanding \Nthan older men, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.20,0:18:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because I observe your orders.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.77,0:18:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What a powerful proof \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.97,0:18:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Word of God endures forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.64,0:18:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,While the advice of human philosophers \Nis frequently flawed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.01,0:18:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible’s counsel works. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.48,0:18:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If we apply it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.49,0:18:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it can help us either \Nto overcome or to cope \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.12,0:18:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with any problem \Nor situation that we may face. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.06,0:18:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.06,0:18:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,by explaining \NGod’s purpose for the future, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.67,0:18:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it gives us a solid hope \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.73,0:18:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,this earth will be restored \Nto the Paradise \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.77,0:18:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was \Nwhen it was first created. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.37,0:18:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be filled \Nwith peace and righteousness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.68,0:18:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What a wonderful gift \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.15,0:18:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave us through the Bible! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.32,0:18:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, languages barriers, \Nopposition from religious leaders,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.89,0:19:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and even \Nan increasingly irreligious world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.43,0:19:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot stop God’s Word.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.20,0:19:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be part \Nof the evidence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.40,0:19:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Word of God \Nendures forever? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.47,0:19:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Read it every day, \Nstudy it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.47,0:19:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,meditate on the deep thoughts \Nthat it contains, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.28,0:19:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and then apply \Nthose priceless teachings in your life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.18,0:19:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way, \Nnot just on the printed page, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.65,0:19:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,not just on the library shelf, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.75,0:19:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but in our minds, \Nin our own hearts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.56,0:19:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in our own lives \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.59,0:19:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the Word of God \Nwill truly endure forever.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.77,0:19:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s get better acquainted \Nwith one of the individuals \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.20,0:19:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we just mentioned \Nwho truly loved God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.21,0:19:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 16th century, \NEnglish scholar William Tyndale \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.61,0:20:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,had to endure harsh persecution \Nin order to translate the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.58,0:20:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was convinced \Nthat the Bible had to be translated. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.26,0:20:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You will notice \Nthat this brief documentary\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.19,0:20:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,has been designed also\Nto appeal to people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.29,0:20:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,who are not \NJehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.43,0:20:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as it will later \Nbe made available \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.60,0:20:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on our official website, \Njw.org.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.12,0:20:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In the autumn of 1536, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.12,0:20:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,William Tyndale was led from his prison cell, \Nin the castle of Vilvoorde, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.50,0:20:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to the site of his impending execution. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.40,0:20:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There a post had been prepared for him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.67,0:20:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyndale was chained to the post, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.24,0:20:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,strangled to death, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.24,0:21:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and then his body burned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.01,0:21:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,before the onlooking crowd. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.01,0:21:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,His crime? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.01,0:21:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyndale struggled to reconcile \Nthe teachings of the church \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.88,0:21:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with his own studies of the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.39,0:21:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,William Tyndale died \Nwith his faith intact \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.66,0:21:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Bible \Nis the Word of God.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.83,0:21:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,William Tyndale \Nwas the first person to seek \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.23,0:21:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to translate the Bible \Nfrom the original languages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.00,0:21:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,into English.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.01,0:21:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyndale was born \Nin the late 15th century. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.24,0:21:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He was born \Nin the area of Gloucestershire \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.38,0:21:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but had a chance to go to Oxford \Nand became a priest.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.52,0:21:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 15th century, \Nthere was a lot of resistance\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.29,0:21:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,—the idea that the Word of God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.29,0:21:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,could just simply be accessible \Nby the general people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.42,0:21:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,People knew the Latin Bible from church, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.69,0:21:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which was interpreted by the priest for them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.40,0:21:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They never had direct access \Nto the Bible themselves.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.77,0:22:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyndale was not allowed \Nto do this translation in England. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.94,0:22:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He went to the Bishop of London \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.97,0:22:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,asking for his permission \Nto translate the New Testament \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.21,0:22:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Greek\N—the original text—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.25,0:22:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,into English \Nbut was not given that permission.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.22,0:22:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Such was the opposition \Nto Bible translation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.02,0:22:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that Tyndale later wrote \Nthat there was \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.12,0:22:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,no place to do it in all England. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.59,0:22:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And so with the help of merchants \Nsympathetic to his cause, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.56,0:22:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyndale fled to Germany \Nwhere he could more easily work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.97,0:22:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,on his English translation \Nof the New Testament. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.10,0:22:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,By 1525, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.11,0:22:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,his translation was complete \Nand ready to be printed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.11,0:22:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The British Library in London \Nholds the answer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.75,0:22:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to what happened next. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.75,0:22:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Karen Limper-Herz, \Na lead curator at the library, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.25,0:22:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to help us find out.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.82,0:22:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are looking \Nat a unique copy of the first edition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.82,0:22:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of Tyndale’s New Testament, \Nprinted in Cologne in 1525. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.99,0:23:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Cologne Fragment \Nis the only known copy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.36,0:23:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of what exists of Tyndale’s first edition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.50,0:23:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of the New Testament. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.20,0:23:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that it is a fragment \Nshows that it was a dangerous thing to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.77,0:23:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The printer had too much to drink \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.34,0:23:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and mentioned that he \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.17,0:23:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,was printing \Nthis pro-Lutheran English New Testament \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.18,0:23:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for somebody called William Tyndale. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.18,0:23:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The authorities found out about it, \Nand the print shop was raided. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.98,0:23:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyndale and his partners ran\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.98,0:23:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—and this is all that survives today—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.99,0:23:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and they went down the Rhine \Na bit further to Worms. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.05,0:23:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fact that they didn’t get much further \Nthan part way through Matthew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.52,0:23:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite indicative \Nof how dangerous it was.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.53,0:23:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The first complete copies \Nof Tyndale’s translation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.06,0:23:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Christian Greek Scriptures \Nwere finally printed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.67,0:23:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in the city of Worms in Germany \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.37,0:23:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1526. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.37,0:23:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Around 3,000 or more \Nof these books were produced.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.58,0:23:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,After leaving Germany, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.59,0:24:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyndale moved to Antwerp. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.66,0:24:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This bustling city \Nwas ideal for Tyndale. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.23,0:24:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It had a thriving printing industry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.83,0:24:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and its busy port \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.93,0:24:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,made it easy for his books \Nto reach readers in England. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.53,0:24:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Guido Latré \Nhas kindly offered to show me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.54,0:24:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,around the very streets that Tyndale \Nwould have walked himself \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.01,0:24:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,some 500 years ago.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.38,0:24:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What he saw around him here \Nwere ordinary people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.21,0:24:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,having access to the Bible in Dutch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.72,0:24:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted the same \Nfor his own folk in England. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.62,0:24:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wanted to smuggle Bibles \Non a large scale into England, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.69,0:24:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,this was Northern Europe’s biggest seaport. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.79,0:24:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can’t easily smuggle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.90,0:24:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a big volume and a big format. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.63,0:24:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So tiny loose leaves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.97,0:24:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that were taken to places like this\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.71,0:24:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,—these underground cellars, \Nthe warehouses—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.71,0:24:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and between the leaves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.98,0:24:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of larger books \Nthat were not forbidden, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.31,0:25:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the tiny leaves of Tyndale’s translation \Nwould have been hidden. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.15,0:25:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In London, \Nsomeone would have recognized: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.55,0:25:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Aha! \NThese are the stacks that are marked. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.22,0:25:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I must have a look at these \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.72,0:25:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and find the loose leaves \Nof Tyndale’s Bible.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.59,0:25:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There were about 30,000 copies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.93,0:25:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of Tyndale’s Bible available \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.93,0:25:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,by the end of his life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.10,0:25:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a brave man \Nand a big man in terms of courage \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.30,0:25:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and in terms of investment of time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.81,0:25:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the risks he took \Nare not to be underestimated.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.74,0:25:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,William Tyndale was imprisoned here\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.11,0:25:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in Vilvoorde, \Njust north of Brussels. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.95,0:25:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As he languished \Nin prison for over a year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.85,0:25:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he no doubt contemplated the cruel death \Nthat inevitably awaited him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.29,0:25:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyndale is often renowned \Nfor his influence on the English language, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.29,0:25:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but his work was more than \Nthat of just scholarly ambition. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.60,0:25:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyndale loved the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.83,0:25:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it can be said of him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.84,0:25:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that he shared the feelings of the psalmist \Nwho spoke of God’s Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.87,0:26:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and said: \N“How I do love your law!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.45,0:26:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite intense opposition,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.68,0:26:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible and the wisdom in it \Nsurvives to this day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.19,0:26:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,a faithful transmission \Nof the original writers’ words. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.99,0:26:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder so many have placed \Nsuch value on the Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.57,0:26:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll be happy to know \Nthat later this month \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.17,0:26:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,an extended version \Nof this documentary \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.60,0:26:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,will be made available. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.61,0:26:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It contains \Nadditional examples of individuals \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.71,0:26:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,who risked their lives \Nto spread God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.28,0:26:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The video is called \NThey Valued the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.05,0:26:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and will be released \Non Video on Demand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.15,0:26:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,under the heading \N“The Bible.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.16,0:26:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that Jehovah \Nis personally involved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.23,0:26:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in preserving \Nand making known his Word, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.33,0:26:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we can be confident \Nthat the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.93,0:26:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is the only true means \Nof drawing close to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.53,0:27:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As a child, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.54,0:27:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,David Sibrey, from England, \Nhad not read the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.87,0:27:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, he had been taught \Ntraditions of men. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.88,0:27:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped him see the truth?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.88,0:27:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born in 1930. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.92,0:27:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We lived in Littlehampton, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.92,0:27:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,which was a seaside town, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.16,0:27:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a very pleasant little place, \Nquiet place.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.06,0:27:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to walk \Nin the countryside. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.46,0:27:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Nature intrigued me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.77,0:27:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,My interest was in what I saw \Nrather than what I read.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.57,0:27:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in 1939, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.47,0:27:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,war broke out, and our road \Nbecame the second line of defense. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.58,0:27:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, of course, \Nyou get the aircraft. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.95,0:27:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there was a young boy \N(younger than myself), \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.45,0:27:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and one Sunday morning \Nan air raid took place, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.45,0:27:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the house \Nwhere he was living \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.62,0:27:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,was destroyed, \Nand he was killed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.62,0:27:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But I remember \Nsaying to my mother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.43,0:28:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why did he have to die?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.06,0:28:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And her answer was: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.26,0:28:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, he’s in a better place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.27,0:28:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s with God in heaven,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.27,0:28:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,which didn’t quite \Nadd up to me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.21,0:28:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t understand \Nhow God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.44,0:28:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,could be responsible \Nfor his death, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.08,0:28:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,which meant \NHe was responsible for war. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.85,0:28:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was—\NThe whole thing was depressing; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.85,0:28:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps put it that way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.99,0:28:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as religion was concerned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.89,0:28:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I accepted it was there, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.89,0:28:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but I couldn’t understand \Nhow it fit in with what was going on. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.46,0:28:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a gap somewhere, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.50,0:28:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and I couldn’t, I couldn’t, plug it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.63,0:28:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time you went to church, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.63,0:28:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you had a hymnbook \Nand a prayer book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.94,0:28:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but a Bible was something \Nyou had personally. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.47,0:28:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only time \NI ever opened it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.01,0:28:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,was when I began to study \Nwith Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.65,0:28:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I was 17 or 18 years of age \Nwhen I started. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.25,0:28:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A brother named Joe Gladwin \Ncalled upon me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.82,0:29:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew nothing about the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.82,0:29:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that he said it, \Nfair enough. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.86,0:29:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He said it was in the Bible, OK. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.06,0:29:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But what do other people say? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.06,0:29:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to look for myself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.83,0:29:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that what Joe \Nwas telling me was right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.34,0:29:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He showed me \Nthat the Bible was true.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.57,0:29:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I began to see that the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.58,0:29:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,told me things \Nthat I had never known. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.68,0:29:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the years, \NI’ve been privileged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.75,0:29:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to collect so many \Ndifferent translations of the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.02,0:29:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading through the different translations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.02,0:29:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s clear that God’s Word never changes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.89,0:29:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I got baptized \Nat the age of 20 in 1950. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.63,0:29:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the years, \NI’ve served first of all as a pioneer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.90,0:29:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,From then I came to Bethel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.90,0:29:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving from Bethel \Nto the circuit and district work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.27,0:29:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and then finally, \Ncoming back to Bethel for the Writing Desk.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.64,0:29:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The assignments I’ve had \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.81,0:29:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,have strengthened my conviction \Nnot only that Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.38,0:30:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is giving direction and his spirit \Ncan enable us to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.48,0:30:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever he wants us to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.25,0:30:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but that the organization has grown and, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.92,0:30:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with the development \Nof the Governing Body’s direction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.46,0:30:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is an organization \Nwhich is second to none. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.83,0:30:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And, therefore, \Nstaying with it is the logical thing to do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.67,0:30:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In my life, \NI looked in many places \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.30,0:30:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for answers \Nto life’s questions, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.61,0:30:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but only the Bible \Nhas provided answers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.58,0:30:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so thankful \Nthat Jehovah continues to teach us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.75,0:30:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Sibrey’s appreciation \Nfor the Bible is heartwarming. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.69,0:30:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember how \Nwe can personally demonstrate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.06,0:30:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,our appreciation \Nfor the Word of God? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.80,0:30:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,By reading, \Nstudying, and meditating \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.73,0:30:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,on the deep thoughts \Nthat it contains \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.97,0:30:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and then by applying \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.34,0:30:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,those inspired teachings \Nin our lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.87,0:31:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When we do that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.14,0:31:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we allow the holy spirit \Nto affect our inner being, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.55,0:31:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to shape our desires \Nand objectives in life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.82,0:31:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,However, what if someone \Nhas harbored resentment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.65,0:31:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,against his fellow man \Nfor years, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.12,0:31:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps to the point \Nof wanting to kill that person? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.56,0:31:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What can God’s Word do \Nin such a serious circumstance?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.06,0:31:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the words \Nof Hebrews 4:12: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.10,0:31:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“For the word of God \Nis alive and exerts power \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.97,0:31:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . and is able to discern \Nthoughts and intentions of the heart.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.61,0:31:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jehovah \Nhas preserved the Bible\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.82,0:31:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can benefit \Nfrom the power of his Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.72,0:31:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Vladimir Olkhov \Nand Valery Zaporozhsky, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.22,0:31:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who are from Russia, \Nwere the fiercest of enemies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.76,0:31:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,yet they experienced \Nthat power firsthand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.31,0:32:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the ringleader of a criminal gang. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.01,0:32:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We extorted money,\Nput people out of business, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.15,0:32:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,threatened them, \Ndragged them away.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.19,0:32:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would hand over everything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.66,0:32:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,People were afraid of me, \Nand I liked it that way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.26,0:32:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I never forgave anybody. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.37,0:32:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone wronged me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.40,0:32:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say: \N“Throw one stone at me! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.84,0:32:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll bury you in a mountain of rocks!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.11,0:32:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1993, \NI was working for the police. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.08,0:32:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They assigned me to gather information \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.02,0:32:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about a gang \Nwhose leader was Vladimir Olkhov.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.59,0:32:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, when committing a crime, \Nthey caught me at the scene.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.73,0:33:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I swore revenge on everybody involved \Nwith my arrest.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.44,0:33:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,During interrogations,\NI did everything \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.48,0:33:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to humiliate Vladimir \Nand tried to break him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.89,0:33:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We just hated each other!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.22,0:33:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I told Valery,\N“Just remember: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.79,0:33:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“Sooner or later \NI’m getting out of prison \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.96,0:33:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you’re a dead man!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.50,0:33:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought to myself:\N‘For a start, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.10,0:33:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’m going to blow up his car. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.10,0:33:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If he doesn’t understand, \Nthen I’ll just eliminate him.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.44,0:33:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,His threats sounded so serious \Nthat I started to fear for my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.15,0:33:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to have my friends \Nand acquaintances \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.95,0:33:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,make his life behind bars unbearable \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.75,0:34:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to make sure \Nthat he would never get out.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.93,0:34:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw that one of my cell mates \Nhad a pocket New Testament. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.03,0:34:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him if I could read it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.10,0:34:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing my interest in spiritual things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.37,0:34:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,someone gave me a Watchtower magazine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.11,0:34:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When I started reading the magazine, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.11,0:34:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that there are \Nother people out there—real people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.38,0:34:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a totally different way \Nof life to be had, even now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.55,0:34:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and with such prospects. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.98,0:34:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just stunned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.28,0:34:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I found another five magazines \Naround the prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.69,0:34:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I devoured them as well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.69,0:34:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I became thoroughly convinced \Nthat I had found the truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.40,0:34:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When my wife was first allowed to visit me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.90,0:34:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I told her right away,\N“I’ve found the truth!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.67,0:34:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife made pretty fast progress\Nand was baptized two years later. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.74,0:34:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Her support was invaluable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.81,0:34:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She would visit me, \Nconstantly encouraging me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.18,0:35:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be faithful \Nand remain loyal to God.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.05,0:35:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1993, \NJehovah’s Witnesses visited me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.19,0:35:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I agreed to a Bible study, \Nbut the truth didn’t touch my heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.20,0:35:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, Jehovah’s Witnesses \Ninvited me to a gathering, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.50,0:35:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and there they told me that Vladimir Olkhov\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.17,0:35:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,—that criminal—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.74,0:35:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,was about to get baptized \Nand become one of Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.41,0:35:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I was cut to the heart! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.88,0:35:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When I got home, \NI burst into tears. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.55,0:35:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that I had to make \Nspiritual progress. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.45,0:35:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if he, \Nin his circumstances, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.45,0:35:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,could do it, then I could do it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.45,0:35:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That very moment,\NI prayed for the first time in my life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.13,0:35:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I was released in October of 1997. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.60,0:35:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,After I was released, \Nthe brothers organized a gathering.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.43,0:35:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They invited me to this gathering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.90,0:35:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember \Nthat as I was approaching the place, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.61,0:36:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly realized this is where \NI once conducted a search!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.31,0:36:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Valery walked into the room. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.11,0:36:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We just hugged each other\Nand burst into tears.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.92,0:36:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw in his eyes \Na completely different look, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.49,0:36:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,not like before\N—it was a kind look. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.59,0:36:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It brought tears to my eyes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.66,0:36:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a big weight \Nwas lifted from my chest. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.46,0:36:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‘My brother!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.83,0:36:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We begged one another for forgiveness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.60,0:36:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,On the 23rd of November 1997, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.27,0:36:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I was baptized together in the same pool \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.48,0:36:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as my new friend Valery.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.85,0:36:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We really became the best of friends. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.82,0:36:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we serve as elders \Nin the same congregation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.29,0:36:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife and I often talk about\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.46,0:36:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,what would have happened to us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.46,0:36:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,if we had not started to study the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.66,0:36:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably we wouldn’t even be alive now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.93,0:37:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve kept our family together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.30,0:37:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Even better, \Nwe now have a spiritual family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.01,0:37:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Christian congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.01,0:37:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And my former enemy \Nis now my brother and best friend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.71,0:37:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, we’ve developed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.85,0:37:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a close relationship with Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.52,0:37:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Only God is able to change the thinking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.52,0:37:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of such bitter enemies as Vlad and I were. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.46,0:37:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I eagerly look forward to the day\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.46,0:37:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when everything that divides people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.46,0:37:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will be gone forever.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.07,0:37:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see \None reason why Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.47,0:37:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,did not allow his Word \Nto be obliterated? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.91,0:37:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew the benefits \Nyou and I would reap \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.32,0:37:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,from having access to the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.85,0:37:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Its message is so powerful, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.19,0:37:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it could help Vladimir and Valery \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.82,0:37:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to change their lives \Nand even become close friends.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.93,0:38:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,While very few of us have taken part \Nin the translation of the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.57,0:38:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us can share it with our neighbors \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.80,0:38:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and help them to gain \Naccurate knowledge of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.41,0:38:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.88,0:38:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,note some of the theocratic activities \Nthat this family enjoys \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.25,0:38:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and what they had to do \Nto become so zealous.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.55,0:38:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, OK. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.48,0:38:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We already know \Nhow this story is going to end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.99,0:39:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No real surprises there.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.69,0:39:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the real question is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.86,0:39:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How did we get here?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.44,0:39:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,For the record, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.47,0:39:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought our ministry \Nreally needed help.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.31,0:39:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife and daughter \Nwere both regular pioneers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.75,0:39:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My son was a solid publisher.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.29,0:39:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And while my schedule \Ndidn’t let me pioneer yet, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.46,0:39:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was trying to do \Nall I could to support them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.80,0:39:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I always assumed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.54,0:39:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the best support I could provide \Nwas just being out with them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.84,0:39:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as much as possible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.81,0:39:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but I quickly realized more was needed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.15,0:40:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Field Service Group Overseer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.15,0:40:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,had been making a real effort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.95,0:40:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to work in the ministry with us \Nregularly the last few weeks, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.66,0:40:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and he kindly mentioned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.66,0:40:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he’d noticed a few challenges.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.13,0:40:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,While our service time was great, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.40,0:40:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he pointed out that our return visits \Nwere slowly dwindling.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.97,0:40:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And other than the studies \NI had with the children, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.07,0:40:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,no one in the family \Nwas conducting a Bible study.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.68,0:40:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him \Nwhat we could do to try \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.78,0:40:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and improve \Nthe quality of our ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.12,0:40:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He showed me Romans 15:19, \Nhighlighting Paul’s words: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.32,0:40:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have thoroughly preached \Nthe good news about the Christ.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.23,0:40:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He suggested \Non our next Family Worship night \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.20,0:40:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,studying Paul’s ministry and seeing \Nwhat we could learn from his example.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.75,0:41:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As we looked at Paul’s ministry, \Nwe realized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.86,0:41:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be more productive \Nwe needed boldness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.09,0:41:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians 6:19 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.40,0:41:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“Pray also for me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.33,0:41:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“that the words may be given to me \Nwhen I open my mouth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.80,0:41:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that I may be able to speak boldly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.91,0:41:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in making known \Nthe sacred secret of the good news.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.81,0:41:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Rina also noticed how Paul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.65,0:41:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,reasoned persuasively with people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.53,0:41:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And Keiko liked how he found \Ncommon ground with those he talked to\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.70,0:42:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,—even referring to a pagan altar \Nto an unknown god \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.97,0:42:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as a way to direct \Nthe conversation to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.44,0:42:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, Haruto noted how 2 Timothy said \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.15,0:42:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul was \N“a workman with nothing to be ashamed of,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.82,0:42:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,handling the word of the truth aright.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.92,0:42:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So he was skilled in using the Scriptures \Nwith those he witnessed to.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.70,0:42:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,See, I told you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.37,0:42:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You already knew \Nhow this was going to end.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.34,0:42:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I started auxiliary pioneering.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.85,0:42:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We now have a number of return visits \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.16,0:43:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and a few progressive Bible studies.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.86,0:43:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But how did we get here? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.03,0:43:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned from the example of Paul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.24,0:43:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and how he \N“thoroughly preached the good news.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.55,0:43:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The group overseer \Ncould’ve simply listed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.08,0:43:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what changes were needed \Nto improve the family’s ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.55,0:43:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, \Nhe directed the father \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.62,0:43:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to a specific principle \Nfound in the Scriptures. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.76,0:43:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, \Nit is only God’s Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.13,0:43:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that “is inspired . . . for teaching.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.73,0:43:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible translations \Nin common languages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.27,0:43:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,started to spread \Nacross Europe in the 1500’s, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.54,0:43:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but it took much longer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.54,0:43:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,for more remote places \Nto receive the Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.51,0:43:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in 1766 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.58,0:43:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that the complete Greek Scriptures, \Nor New Testament, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.02,0:43:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,was first published in Greenlandic\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.75,0:44:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,—a language spoken today \Nby about 50,000 people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.26,0:44:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In August of last year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.56,0:44:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the privilege of serving \Na regional convention in Greenland, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.63,0:44:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,which is overseen \Nby the Scandinavia branch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.90,0:44:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Greenland is the neighbor \Nto the north of Newfoundland, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.64,0:44:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,where I pioneered for 11 years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.97,0:44:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was a wonderful experience \Nto go there and meet our brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.91,0:44:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Some 400 brothers and sisters \Ntraveled at their own expense \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.72,0:44:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from all over Scandinavia to support \Nthe convention in Greenland. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.36,0:44:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Although Greenland is a land \Ncovered by large ice caps, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.06,0:44:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there are many warm hearts \Nyearning for the truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.07,0:44:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that Jesus had Greenland in mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.64,0:45:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,when he spoke about preaching \Nto the most distant part of the earth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.78,0:45:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Arne Mattsson. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.88,0:45:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife, Karin, and I have lived \Nin Greenland for more than 34 years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.02,0:45:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We have traveled all over the country \Npreaching about God’s Kingdom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.53,0:45:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have had \Nsome fantastic experiences.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.90,0:45:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 1950’s, two young special pioneers\N came to Greenland \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.43,0:45:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as the first publishers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.67,0:45:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They traveled by boat \Nfrom town to town \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.41,0:45:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,carrying just tents \Nand simple equipment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.48,0:45:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They had to endure \Nthe cold weather, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.01,0:45:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,face resistance \Nfrom the local ministers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.58,0:45:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and even fight with sledge dogs \Nthat took their food. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.48,0:45:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But they laid the groundwork \Nfor the great effort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.99,0:45:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that has been made \Nto preach to all in this country.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.59,0:45:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 1960’s and ’70’s, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.53,0:45:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,many families \Nmoved here from Denmark \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.10,0:45:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to help with the preaching work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.17,0:45:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember how I, \Nas a teenager in 1971, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.47,0:45:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,moved from Denmark \Nto Greenland with my family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.84,0:46:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not easy \Nto learn the language, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.04,0:46:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but the brothers and sisters \Nfrom Denmark did their best, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.91,0:46:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it had a good effect \Non the territory.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.78,0:46:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1973, The Watchtower began \Nto be published in Greenlandic. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.89,0:46:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to pronounce the name, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.89,0:46:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Napassuliak’ Alapernaerssuivfik, \Nwas a challenge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.29,0:46:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But it has been a popular magazine \Nin Greenland ever since. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.53,0:46:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Once, we met a couple \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.57,0:46:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who for many years \Nhad received copies of The Watchtower \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.90,0:46:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,when publishers visited their settlement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.17,0:46:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They told us that they often felt depressed \Nwhen they woke up in the morning, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.11,0:46:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but when they read the magazine, \Nthey felt better. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.21,0:46:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would read \Nthe same copies over and over again.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.02,0:46:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When the temperature drops \Nand the snow falls, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.16,0:46:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the landscape gets covered \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.16,0:46:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,by a beautiful white blanket for half a year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.83,0:47:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so the publishers \Nmake good use of the summer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.84,0:47:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Some towns and settlements \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.71,0:47:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,only seldom receive a witness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.01,0:47:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no roads between the towns, \Nbut we reach isolated areas by boat. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.38,0:47:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When someone shows interest \Nin our message, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.38,0:47:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the contact \Nis maintained by phone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.29,0:47:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Many have great respect for the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.36,0:47:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and so My Book of Bible Stories \Nhas found its way into many, many homes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.29,0:47:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Over a period of 24 years, \NKarin and I have sailed so much \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.60,0:47:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that it equals a trip \Ntwice around the globe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.47,0:47:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This has cost a lot of effort and money, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.97,0:47:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but with Jehovah’s blessing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.24,0:47:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we have been able \Nto continue year after year \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.51,0:47:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,preaching to the distant parts \Nof Greenland. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.05,0:47:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The preaching work here \Nis a great experience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.12,0:47:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,People are attentive and kind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.42,0:47:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But it took a long time \Nbefore the first native Greenlander \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.73,0:48:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,was baptized\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.73,0:48:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—actually 18 years of zealous preaching. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.10,0:48:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, there are \Nmore than 150 publishers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.57,0:48:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in 5 congregations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.64,0:48:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has really blessed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.64,0:48:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the work that has been done here \Nfor more than 60 years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.06,0:48:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In August 2016, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.89,0:48:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a very special convention \Nwas held in the capital of Nuuk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.49,0:48:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters \Nfrom all over Scandinavia \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.97,0:48:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,traveled all the way \Nto attend the convention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.61,0:48:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We were very encouraged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.61,0:48:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,by the visit of a member \Nof the Governing Body, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.78,0:48:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Mark Sanderson, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.78,0:48:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who gave us \Nsome faith-strengthening talks.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.65,0:48:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it’s a great privilege \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.39,0:49:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to understand the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.49,0:49:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s amazing that Jehovah \Ngave his attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.49,0:49:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to an insignificant human like me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.53,0:49:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When I started to follow \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.53,0:49:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible’s unique teachings \Nand principles, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.00,0:49:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I clearly understood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.21,0:49:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how it would benefit my own life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.81,0:49:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,After this convention, \Neven though we live in small towns \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.88,0:49:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,far away \Nfrom the rest of the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.08,0:49:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we feel closer than ever before \Nto the worldwide brotherhood.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.59,0:49:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The peak attendance \Nat the convention was 614\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.03,0:49:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,—the largest ever in Greenland. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.57,0:49:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers \Nfrom other parts of Scandinavia \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.17,0:49:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,who attended \Nthe convention also took part\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.71,0:49:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in a campaign \Ninviting interested ones. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.24,0:49:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In only two hours, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.51,0:49:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole capital city of Nuuk \Nwas covered. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.41,0:50:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a wonderful witness!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.08,0:50:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And speaking of witnessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.15,0:50:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in “the most distant part \Nof the earth,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.15,0:50:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll be happy to know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.79,0:50:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that Brother Geoffrey Jackson \Nof the Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.66,0:50:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,recently explained \Nin a morning worship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.26,0:50:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how the Bible was translated \Ninto numerous languages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.00,0:50:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 19th century. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.00,0:50:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That segment is now available \Non Video on Demand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.94,0:50:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It is entitled \NReaching “the Most Distant Part.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.07,0:50:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And later this month, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.34,0:50:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,a beautiful segment \Nfrom the 2011 annual meeting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.01,0:50:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,will be posted \Nfor your enjoyment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.12,0:50:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It is an interview \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.12,0:50:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with five widows \Nof Governing Body members. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.65,0:50:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The sisters relate \Nhow they learned the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.96,0:50:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and share treasured memories \Nfrom their many years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.26,0:50:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of faithful service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.10,0:50:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This segment is entitled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.56,0:50:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Interview With Faithful Sisters\N—Widows of Governing Body Members \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.54,0:50:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and will be available \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.17,0:51:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,on Video on Demand under the \N“Interviews and Experiences” category.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.71,0:51:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you agree that Jehovah gave us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.71,0:51:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,an outstanding gift in his Word? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.88,0:51:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He not only gave us the gift \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.32,0:51:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but also made sure time and time again \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.22,0:51:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was preserved for our benefit.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.53,0:51:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Individuals we met earlier in the program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.90,0:51:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,such as Brothers David Sibrey, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.50,0:51:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Vladimir Olkhov, \Nand Valery Zaporozhsky, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.74,0:51:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,have all seen \Nthe effects of the power \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.57,0:51:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that God’s Word exerts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.87,0:51:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and the guidance it provides. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.91,0:51:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We also saw that the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.05,0:51:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is “beneficial for teaching” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.08,0:51:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and “for setting things straight,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.15,0:51:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as we watched a family \Nlearn how to improve their ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.09,0:51:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by following the example \Nof the apostle Paul. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.92,0:51:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, God’s Word has endured \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.86,0:51:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and will continue to endure forever.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.63,0:52:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,As you know, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.27,0:52:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,on April 3, 2017, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.87,0:52:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,our museums in Warwick \Nwill open to the public. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.44,0:52:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition \Nto our enlarged gallery entitled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.44,0:52:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Bible and the Divine Name,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.45,0:52:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we will also have \Na new gallery on the theme \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.92,0:52:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Word of God Endures Forever.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.92,0:52:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come and visit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.92,0:52:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll be happy to see \Na wonderful collection of Bibles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.39,0:52:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that illustrates the points \Nwe have discussed in this broadcast.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.50,0:52:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The psalmist was inspired to write: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.93,0:52:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“How I do love your law!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.17,0:52:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And we agree. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.17,0:52:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We love Jehovah \Nand we love the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.21,0:52:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and so have millions \Nthroughout the centuries, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.25,0:52:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,including those who were used \Nby Jehovah to preserve his Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.85,0:52:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,With these thoughts in mind, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.02,0:52:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s enjoy \Nthis month’s music video entitled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.82,0:53:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Word Endures Forever.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.18,0:53:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They looked up at the stars\NWith godly fear in their hearts.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.92,0:53:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They thanked their God up above\NFor revealing to them His love.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.57,0:53:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So You gave them your name,\NA Kingdom hope to proclaim.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.08,0:54:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re words preserved for our day.\NThey’re faithful words to show us the way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.12,0:54:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They loved you from their heart,\NAnd they were proud to play their part—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.76,0:54:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Approved by you to preserve your Word,\NWrote it down so you would be heard.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.31,0:54:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Word endures forever,\NAnd your sayings are, oh, so deep.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.55,0:54:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The good news you declare \Nis a breath of fresh air,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.66,0:54:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And your sayings I just want to keep.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.03,0:54:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, whatever Your enemies tried,\NThey could not silence You.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.34,0:55:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Your loyal ones who loved your Word\NKept their faith, integrity too.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.32,0:55:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they tried to ban their Bibles,\NThey were prepared to give their lives.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.43,0:55:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For so strong was their faith \Nand the witness they gave,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.17,0:55:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Not one of your words was erased.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.90,0:55:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And so your Word endures forever,\NAnd your sayings are, oh, so deep.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.88,0:55:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The good news you declare \Nis a breath of fresh air,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.45,0:55:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And your sayings I just want to keep.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.46,0:55:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And you told us your name is Jehovah.\NIn your Word it’s plain to see.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.60,0:56:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So your name will endure,\NAll your words will come true,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.14,0:56:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll praise you all of our days.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.15,0:56:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So your Word endures forever,\NAnd your sayings are, oh, so deep.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.69,0:56:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The good news you declare \Nis a breath of fresh air,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.83,0:56:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And your sayings I just want to keep,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.97,0:56:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All of my days.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.85,0:56:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A beautiful song, indeed!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.12,0:56:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We would like to conclude \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.19,0:56:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,this program \Nby sharing these greetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.19,0:56:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from our brothers and sisters in Mali. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.06,0:56:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mali is located in western Africa, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.96,0:57:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,reaching well into the Sahara Desert. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.13,0:57:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The northern part of the country \Nis hot and covered with sand, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.90,0:57:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but the southern region, \Nwhich is watered by the Niger River, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.34,0:57:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is green with forests and vegetation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.51,0:57:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Witnesses in the country \Nhave a huge task, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.22,0:57:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,as the ratio \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses to population \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.42,0:57:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is about one publisher \Nto 59,000 residents. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.16,0:57:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the distances are tremendous. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.36,0:57:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The approximately 300 publishers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.00,0:57:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,cover an area more than twice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.00,0:57:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the size of the country of France.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.73,0:57:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mali is one of the hottest countries \Nin the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.27,0:57:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so some groups and congregations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.44,0:57:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,hold their meetings outdoors \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.44,0:57:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,under the cool shade of a tree.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.61,0:57:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Although the official language \Nof the country is French, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.31,0:57:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,most people better understand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.68,0:57:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the local language Bambara. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.05,0:57:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, most meetings are either \Nheld or interpreted in Bambara. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.62,0:58:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, language classes \Nwere held in Bomu, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.39,0:58:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which is another local language.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.73,0:58:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the seven publishers \Nof the American Sign Language group \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.50,0:58:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,have been assigned to witness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.50,0:58:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to the more than \N350,000 people in Mali \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.51,0:58:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,who have \Na hearing impairment.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.87,0:58:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year, the total attendance \Nfor the Memorial \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.91,0:58:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was over 1,100 people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.11,0:58:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,One man who received an invitation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.35,0:58:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,walked three kilometers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.69,0:58:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or almost two miles, \Nto attend the Memorial \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.12,0:58:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,despite having \Na physical challenge with his foot. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.72,0:58:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He is now regular at the meetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.13,0:58:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and is making good progress.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.83,0:58:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, a new Kingdom Hall \Nwas built in the capital city. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.63,0:58:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Municipal and state authorities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.07,0:58:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,neighbors, and many passersby \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.44,0:58:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,have been amazed \Nat what they have seen, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.91,0:58:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have praised \Nthe brothers working on the project.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.84,0:58:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters \Nin Mali send us their love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.25,0:58:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We love them, \Nand we love all of you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.02,0:59:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.62,0:59:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,from the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.47,0:02:06.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹 歴史的瞬間へようこそ！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.71,0:02:10.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,スタジオが ニューヨーク州\Nウォーウィックの新しい世界本部から—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.41,0:02:14.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほど近くに移動しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.25,0:02:17.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しいスタジオでの\N最初のプログラムから— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.19,0:02:20.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,たくさんの霊的宝石をお届けします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.89,0:02:23.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず どんな障害を乗り越えて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.43,0:02:27.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,一般の人たちが神の言葉を読めるように\Nなったでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.50,0:02:30.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,英国のウィリアム・ティンダルが\N示した勇気についての—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.70,0:02:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,興奮を誘う\Nドキュメンタリーです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.47,0:02:39.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,かつて憎み合っていた二人が\N親友になれたのは なぜでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.01,0:02:44.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,この話から 聖書の一致させる力が\N分かるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.31,0:02:49.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教で進歩するため\N使徒パウロから何を学べるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.59,0:02:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,晩の家族の崇拝に参加しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.26,0:02:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 1月のJW Broadcastingです！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.75,0:03:20.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは エホバの証人として\N聖書を本当に大切にしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.95,0:03:22.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜですか？ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.75,0:03:25.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書は神の言葉だからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.86,0:03:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それゆえ 聖書を読み 学び \Nその歴史を喜んで調べるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.73,0:03:34.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,少し立ち止まって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.26,0:03:38.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,過去幾世紀にもわたってなされて来た\N聖書を妨害し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.33,0:03:42.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,その頒布さえも阻止しようとした\N多くの試みについて考えると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.94,0:03:45.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のことは明らかです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.07,0:03:48.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは その著者である\Nエホバ神ご自身が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.61,0:03:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その貴重な言葉を保存し 知らせることに\N関与しておられたということです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.45,0:04:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはイザヤ 40章8節の言葉と\N見事に調和しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.19,0:04:04.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,“青草は干からび 花は枯れた”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.46,0:04:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかし わたしたちの神の言葉は\N 定めのない時に至るまで保つのである”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.90,0:04:13.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,この点を念頭に置いて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.94,0:04:18.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月はわたしがいつも\N心にかけている事柄をお話しします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.68,0:04:23.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は\N“神の言葉は永久に存続する”です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.88,0:04:27.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは神の言葉の価値を\N認識すればするほど—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.55,0:04:30.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,それをもっと読みたいと\N願うようになり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.29,0:04:35.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに重要なことに それを生活に\N当てはめるようになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.46,0:04:38.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ神は人に霊感を与えて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.29,0:04:41.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分の貴重な言葉を\N書き記させたとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.20,0:04:44.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,貴重な贈り物を与えてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.23,0:04:47.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,書き記された神の言葉を通してのみ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.04,0:04:51.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは神の愛の深さについて\N学べるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.24,0:04:54.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,その言葉は生きていくための\N道しるべです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.78,0:04:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それには 人を創造した目的が\N記されています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.12,0:05:01.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和と幸福の内に得られる—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.38,0:05:06.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠の命の貴重な神の約束が\N記されています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.72,0:05:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒パウロが テモテ第二 3章16, 17節で\N霊感の下に記したことは当を得ています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.83,0:05:19.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,“聖書全体は神の霊感を受けたもので—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.87,0:05:27.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,“教え 戒め 物事を正し \N 義にそって訓育するのに有益です”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.51,0:05:30.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それは 神の人が十分な能力を備え—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.91,0:05:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あらゆる良い業に対して\N 全く整えられた者となるためです” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.82,0:05:40.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,むろんサタン悪魔は\N人々が天の父エホバからの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.99,0:05:45.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,この貴重な真理に接することを\N望んでいません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.63,0:05:51.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の入手を困難にする多くの障害が\Nあったのもうなずけます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.67,0:05:56.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンが背後でそのすべてを\N操っていたわけではないものの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.04,0:05:59.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,それらを利用したことは明らかです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.41,0:06:04.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな障害が どのように\N克服されてきたのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.21,0:06:09.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初に 言語という障壁について\N考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.75,0:06:15.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,旧約聖書とも呼ばれる\N聖書の最初の39冊の書は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.02,0:06:19.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,主にヘブライ語で書かれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.06,0:06:24.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの書はヘブライ語を話す\Nエホバの僕たちによって知られていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.50,0:06:29.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 時の経過と共に\Nとりわけバビロン滅亡後に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.21,0:06:35.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人の多くは他の国民の中に\N自分たちの共同体を作りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.14,0:06:41.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,その多くはギリシャ語を話し\Nもはやヘブライ語を用いなくなりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.82,0:06:45.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは 理解できる言語で\N聖書に接することが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.22,0:06:48.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,もはやできなくなったという意味です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.06,0:06:50.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,次に何が生じましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.66,0:06:56.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,アレクサンドロス大王が\N当時の世界を次々と征服していった結果—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.03,0:07:03.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギリシャ語は徐々にその帝国内で\N商業と政治の共通語となっていきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.04,0:07:06.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギリシャ語を話す\N広大な地域に散在しているユダヤ人や—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.98,0:07:11.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ教に改宗した人たちに\N聖書が理解されるためには—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.71,0:07:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギリシャ語に翻訳される\N必要がありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:19.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,西暦前250年ごろから—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.92,0:07:24.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘブライ語聖書はギリシャ語に\N翻訳されるようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.96,0:07:27.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがてそのギリシャ語訳は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.10,0:07:31.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,セプトゥアギンタ訳\Nとして知られるようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.07,0:07:35.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは 西暦1世紀にギリシャ語を話す\Nクリスチャンたちによって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:39.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,広く頻繁に用いられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.58,0:07:44.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際 クリスチャン・ギリシャ語聖書\Nつまり新約聖書の筆者たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.51,0:07:49.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,その翻訳から頻繁に直接引用しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.29,0:07:52.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,このようにして\Nその障害は克服されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.76,0:07:56.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし さらに多くの\N言語の障壁がありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.96,0:07:59.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ローマ帝国が繁栄するようになると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.93,0:08:03.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギリシャ語に代わってラテン語が\N共通語になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.97,0:08:08.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,今度は 聖書をラテン語に翻訳する\N必要が生じました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.97,0:08:13.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラテン語の聖書翻訳が\Nいくつか登場するようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.91,0:08:18.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし ヒエロニムスがラテン語の\N聖書全体の翻訳を完成したのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.78,0:08:22.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,西暦405年のことでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.45,0:08:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはラテン語ウルガタ訳として\N知られるようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.12,0:08:31.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヒエロニムスの翻訳は\N次の千年あまりの期間—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.89,0:08:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,キリスト教世界において\N標準聖書となりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.67,0:08:42.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし ラテン語はすぐに\N教育のあるエリートの言語となったため—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.61,0:08:48.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,一般の人々は聖書の音信を\Nもはや理解できなくなりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.54,0:08:50.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,その長い期間のうちに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.68,0:08:57.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の一部を 他のいくつかの言語で\N翻訳した誠実な人々がいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.45,0:09:03.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし それらの翻訳はもちろん\Nすべて手書きによるものでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.23,0:09:08.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした手書きの聖書は\N数が少なく高価でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.03,0:09:12.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 自分の言語あるいは\N一般の言語で読める聖書の数は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.60,0:09:15.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に限られていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.37,0:09:22.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 言語だけが神の言葉の進展を脅かす\N唯一の障害だったわけではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.04,0:09:24.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,2つ目の要素があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.38,0:09:31.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは聖書の翻訳と頒布に対する\N宗教指導者の直接の反対です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.62,0:09:36.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,その反対は1229年\Nトゥールーズの宗教会議において—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.83,0:09:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,地元の教会が次の布告をした時から\N増し加わりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.33,0:09:50.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,“我々はまた平信徒が旧約および\N 新約聖書を持つことを禁じる”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.17,0:09:55.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,1234年にタラゴナ教会会議は\Nこう布告しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.95,0:10:02.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,“何人たりとも自国語で旧約 および\N 新約聖書を所有してはならない”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.52,0:10:04.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,“もし所有している者がいるなら—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.95,0:10:09.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,“この布告の発令から8日以内に\N それらを地元の司教に提出させ—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.99,0:10:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それらを焼き払うように”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.20,0:10:19.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうして歴史上\N非常に長い期間にわたって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.94,0:10:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,一般の人々の話す言語で聖書を読むことは\Nほとんどできなかったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.01,0:10:32.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし それは神の言葉がずっと\N存続できないという意味でしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.05,0:10:35.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,言語の障壁も\N宗教指導者たちの反対も—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.75,0:10:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉が広く知られるのを\N阻止することはできませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.82,0:10:47.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした暗黒時代にあっても\N神の言葉を愛し それを懸命に翻訳し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.50,0:10:51.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々がそれを入手できるように\Nした者たちがいたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.97,0:10:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジョン・ウィクリフとロラード派と\N呼ばれるその追随者たちがいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.24,0:11:06.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジョン・ウィクリフとその仲間たちは\N1382年ごろ英訳聖書を完成しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.78,0:11:10.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,翻訳した聖書の手書きのコピーを\N熱心に作成し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.62,0:11:15.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,村から村を回わり\N人々に聖書を読んだのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.79,0:11:21.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,教会のすさまじい反対にもかかわらず\Nウィクリフと追随者たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.06,0:11:27.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,心の正直な多くの人々が\N英語で聖書を入手できるようにしたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.80,0:11:30.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,1384年のウィクリフの死後—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.97,0:11:35.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,その追随者たちには\N厳しい反対が臨みました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.78,0:11:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの者たちの土地や所有物は没収され\N火あぶりにされた人もいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.35,0:11:46.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウィクリフとロラード派の\N行なったことに対応して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.56,0:11:54.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,1408年 カンタベリーの大司教であった\Nトマス･アランデルはこう述べました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.83,0:11:59.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,“したがって我々は\N 次のことを布告し 定める”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.84,0:12:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“今後は何人も自らの権威で 聖書本文を\N 英語や他の言語に翻訳してはならない”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.21,0:12:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そうする者は破門の痛みが伴うであろう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.32,0:12:20.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,このような反対は聖書を翻訳し広める\N努力を一掃してしまったでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.56,0:12:23.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのようなことはありません！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.59,0:12:28.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウィクリフと追随者たちの働きは\N英国や中央ヨーロッパにおいてさえ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.96,0:12:32.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書への関心を高める結果となりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.90,0:12:38.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,宗教指導者たちは神の言葉を\N沈黙させることはできませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.87,0:12:43.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,事実 ウィクリフの死後\Nわずか数十年たった後— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.05,0:12:49.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書が驚異的に広まるのに役立った\N２つの要素が生じました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.15,0:12:52.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初のものは1454年ごろに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.39,0:12:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,組み替えできる活字を用いた\N印刷技術が発達したことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.30,0:13:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この発明によって多くの言語で\N大量の聖書を印刷できるようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.40,0:13:12.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,2番目の要素はヘブライ語および\Nギリシャ語原文による聖書本文の—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.64,0:13:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,収集と印刷が行なわれたことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.51,0:13:23.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,これにより多くの翻訳者たちは\N原文で聖書本文を入手できるようになり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.39,0:13:29.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分たちの言語で質の高い翻訳を\N行なえるようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.76,0:13:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その結果は？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.03,0:13:36.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,1500年代にはヨーロッパ中で\N新しい翻訳が行なわれ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.53,0:13:40.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,一般の人々の言語で印刷されたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.77,0:13:47.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,それらは ドイツ語 英語 イタリア語\Nフランス語 オランダ語 チェコ語— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.01,0:13:49.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,デンマーク語 スウェーデン語—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.11,0:13:54.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,スペイン語 スロベニア語\Nその他多くあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.22,0:13:57.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 反対は続きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.85,0:14:02.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書翻訳者たちは異端審問によって\Nたびたび追い回され—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.42,0:14:05.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウィリアム・ティンダルや\Nジョン・ロジャーズのように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.23,0:14:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,殺害された翻訳者たちもいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:13.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,にもかかわらず\N神の言葉は引き続き存続し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.94,0:14:18.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ますます多くの言語で\N入手できるようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.91,0:14:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,1800年代の初期までに\N聖書翻訳は勢いを増し加えはじめました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.28,0:14:31.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書協会や勇敢な翻訳者たちは\N地の様々な場所で仕事を始め—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.05,0:14:36.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがてアジア アフリカ\N太平洋の島々の言語で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.09,0:14:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,また アメリカ大陸の土着の言語でも\N聖書が読めるようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.40,0:14:51.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,1800年から1899年にかけて\N聖書の一部が400の言語に翻訳され—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.44,0:14:59.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,1900年から1950年にかけて\Nさらに500以上の言語が加えられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.45,0:15:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「新世界訳聖書」が成し遂げたこと\N について考えてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.92,0:15:08.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月までに「新世界訳聖書」は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.79,0:15:13.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,その全部あるいは一部が\N149の言語で出版され—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.96,0:15:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに 37の言語が承認されています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.30,0:15:23.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 言語の障壁も\N宗教指導者の反対も—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.67,0:15:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉の頒布を阻止できなかった\Nことは明らかです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.55,0:15:33.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが\Nずっと保護してこられたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.18,0:15:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは 詩編 12編6, 7節が\N述べる通りです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.25,0:15:42.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバのみことばは浄いことば—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.12,0:15:47.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,“地の溶鉱炉で精錬され\N 七度純化された銀のようだ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.20,0:15:51.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバよ あなたご自身が\N 彼らを守ってくださいます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.20,0:15:54.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたは この世代から\N 定めのない時に至るまで—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.84,0:15:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ひとりびとりを\N 保護してくださるのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.67,0:16:01.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです エホバはこの時代まで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.38,0:16:06.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分の語られたそれぞれの\N貴重な言葉を保護してこられたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.65,0:16:10.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 3つ目の障害について\N考えてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.89,0:16:17.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書は 今やおよそ3000の言語で\N全体あるいはその一部が入手できますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.36,0:16:21.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの人はそれを読むことに無関心です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.43,0:16:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,現代では人々はますます懐疑的になり\N宗教心がありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.07,0:16:30.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,科学者たちは進化論を称揚し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.77,0:16:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聡明な人なら神の存在を疑うと\N思い込ませています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.31,0:16:38.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,同時に 世の哲学は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.18,0:16:45.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分にとって正しいと思えるところに従って\N人生を決定するよう人々に勧めています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.15,0:16:47.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,結果はどうですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.26,0:16:53.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々が自分の利己的で肉的な欲望に\N導かれる世界の誕生です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.50,0:16:55.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,幸福になるどころか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.16,0:17:00.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの人は空しくて\N満足感のない状況にあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.74,0:17:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この障害はどのように\N克服されていますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.44,0:17:12.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中で人々は神の言葉 聖書を開き\N自分でそれを読んでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.01,0:17:18.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,それが単なる人間の知恵から出たもの\Nではないことに 人々は気付いています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.29,0:17:24.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,その原則を生活に当てはめることにより\N満足と喜びを味わっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.66,0:17:29.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,創造者が示される正しい道徳規準に\N従って生きることにより—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.03,0:17:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自尊心と尊厳を保っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.14,0:17:39.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 119編97-100節が\N述べるとおりです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.98,0:17:43.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしはどんなにあなたの律法を\N 愛していることでしょう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.35,0:17:46.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それは一日じゅう\N わたしの思いとなっています”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.62,0:17:49.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたのおきては\N わたしを敵よりも賢くし—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.79,0:17:52.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それは定めのない時に至るまで\N わたしのものです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.79,0:17:56.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,“すべての教師に勝る洞察力を\N 得るようになりました”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.36,0:17:59.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたの諭しが\N わたしの思いとなっているからです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.60,0:18:03.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしは年長者に勝る\N 理解力をもって行動します”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.47,0:18:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたの命令を守り行なったからです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.67,0:18:14.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉が永久に存続することを示す\N何という強力な証なのでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.01,0:18:18.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間の哲学者の助言には\Nたびたび欠陥が見つかりますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.71,0:18:21.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の助言はそうではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.95,0:18:23.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを当てはめるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.52,0:18:26.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,直面するかもしれない\Nどんな問題や状況でも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.72,0:18:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,克服したり対処したりするのに\N助けとなります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.43,0:18:36.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに 将来に対する神の目的が\N説明されているので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.83,0:18:40.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,この地球が 当初創造されたときと\N同じパラダイスに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.84,0:18:45.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,回復されるという確かな希望を\N得ることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.87,0:18:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこには平和と義が行き渡ります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.08,0:18:55.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは聖書を通して 何と素晴らしい\N贈り物をくださったのでしょう！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.12,0:19:00.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです 言語の障壁も\N宗教指導者の反対も—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.02,0:19:06.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,増し加わる世の無関心も\N神の言葉をとどめることはできません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.80,0:19:13.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたはどのようにして神の言葉が\N永久に存続することの証拠を示せますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.74,0:19:20.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎日それを読んで 学び \Nそこに含まれている深い考えを黙想し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.34,0:19:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,計り知れない価値を持つ\Nその教えを生活に当てはめてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.88,0:19:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのようにして印刷されたページや\N図書棚にではなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.26,0:19:38.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの思いと心に\Nまた自分たちの生活において—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.73,0:19:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉はまさに永久に\N存続することになるでしょう！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.83,0:19:52.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 先程述べた 神の言葉を真に愛した人を\Nさらに取り上げましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:56.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,16世紀 英国の学者\Nウィリアム・ティンダルは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.25,0:20:01.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を翻訳するため 厳しい迫害に\N耐えなければなりませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.32,0:20:02.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでもティンダルは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.78,0:20:07.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書は翻訳されなければならない\Nと確信していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.49,0:20:09.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,この短いドキュメンタリーは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.56,0:20:14.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人ではない人も\N楽しめるよう作られています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.63,0:20:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,後ほど 公式ウェブサイト\Njw.orgに掲載されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.89,0:20:43.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,1536年の秋\Nウィリアム・ティンダルは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.33,0:20:47.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,刑務所の独房から\Nビルボールデ城へ連行されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.63,0:20:49.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼の処刑場です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.90,0:20:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,杭が用意されており\N彼は鎖で縛りつけられ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.10,0:21:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,絞殺され\N遺体は公衆の面前で焼かれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.98,0:21:05.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼の罪状は 教会の教えを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.95,0:21:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ティンダル自身の聖書の研究に\N調和させようと奮闘したことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.29,0:21:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ティンダルは 聖書が神の言葉である\Nとの信仰を保ったまま死にました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.03,0:21:26.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウィリアム・ティンダルは原語の聖書を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.50,0:21:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,英語に翻訳しようと努めた最初の人でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.21,0:21:33.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ティンダルは 15世紀の終わりごろ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.81,0:21:36.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,グロースターシャー近郊で生まれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.51,0:21:41.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,のちにオックスフォードへ行き司祭になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.78,0:21:46.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時 神の言葉を一般の人々にも\N入手しやすくするべきだ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.46,0:21:49.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,という運動が盛んでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.66,0:21:55.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々は教会で ラテン語聖書の独自の解釈を\N司祭から教えられていましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.50,0:21:59.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を直接 手にすることは\Nありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.47,0:22:03.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,イングランドで聖書翻訳は\N禁じられていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.04,0:22:07.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこで ティンダルは\Nロンドン司教に許可を求めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.01,0:22:11.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,新約聖書を原語のギリシャ語から\N英語に翻訳するためです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.35,0:22:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 許可はおりませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.35,0:22:20.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書翻訳に対する反対がとても激しかったので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.82,0:22:22.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,ティンダルはのちに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.32,0:22:27.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,翻訳できる場所は イングランドのどこにも\Nなかったと述べています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.33,0:22:31.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 彼の活動に賛同する\N商人たちからの援助もあり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.33,0:22:35.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,新約聖書の英訳に取り組みやすい\Nドイツへ逃げました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.84,0:22:41.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,1525年には翻訳が完成し\N印刷の用意ができました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.58,0:22:43.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロンドンの大英図書館には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.38,0:22:46.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 どうなったかを\N示すものが残されています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.58,0:22:51.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,主任学芸員のカレン・リンパーヘルツ博士\Nにお聞きしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.95,0:22:55.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは ティンダルの新約聖書の\N貴重な初版で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.39,0:22:58.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,1525年にケルンで印刷されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.59,0:23:03.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ケルン断片はティンダル訳の初版として\N唯一現存しているものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.43,0:23:07.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,これが断片だという事実は \N危険な作業だったことを示しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.90,0:23:11.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,酒に酔った印刷業者が\N“自分はティンダルのために—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.24,0:23:15.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,“親ルター派の英訳聖書を印刷している”\N ともらしてしまいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.71,0:23:19.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを知った当局は\N印刷所を襲撃しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.41,0:23:22.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ティンダルたちはライン川をたどり\Nウォルムスへ逃げ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.82,0:23:25.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのときの断片が\N現在まで生き延びています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.95,0:23:28.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らがマタイによる書しか\N手にしていないことも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.66,0:23:32.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,危険な作業だったことを示しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.49,0:23:35.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ティンダル訳の最初の\Nクリスチャン・ギリシャ語聖書は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.43,0:23:42.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,最終的に 1526年\Nドイツのウォルムスで印刷されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.77,0:23:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから3000冊以上出版されたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.59,0:24:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドイツを離れた後 ティンダルは\Nアントワープに向かいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.16,0:24:04.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,この活気ある都市は\N彼にとって理想の地でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.99,0:24:06.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,印刷産業が盛んで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.86,0:24:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,往来の盛んな港からイングランドへ\N聖書を届けやすくなったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.87,0:24:17.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,グイド・ラトレ教授は およそ500年前に\Nティンダル自身が歩いたであろう—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.11,0:24:21.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,まさにその道を案内してくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.51,0:24:26.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼はここで 普通の人が聖書を母語で\N手にしている様子を目にし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.98,0:24:30.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,故郷のイングランドでも\N同じようにしたいと思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.82,0:24:34.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,イングランドに\N大量の聖書をひそかに送るのに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.82,0:24:39.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,北ヨーロッパ最大の港町は\Nちょうど良い場所でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.19,0:24:44.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,大きな本をそのままひそかに送るのは\N簡単なことではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.53,0:24:47.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこで 細かくページを分けて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.67,0:24:51.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,地下倉庫や貯蔵所などに\N持ち込まれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.07,0:24:55.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 発禁文書ではない\N大きな本の間に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.08,0:24:59.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ティンダル訳の小さなページが\N隠されたようです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.21,0:25:03.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロンドンで ある人たちは \N“あぁ これが例の本だ！—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.59,0:25:07.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,“よく見て この中から\N ティンダルの聖書のページを見つけないと”—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.66,0:25:10.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,と気づいたことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.03,0:25:12.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼の生涯の終わりまでには—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.09,0:25:16.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,3万冊ものティンダル訳が\N入手できるようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.83,0:25:23.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,勇気においても 費やした時間の点でも\N彼は勇敢で偉大な人物です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.57,0:25:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,また おかした危険も過小評価できません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.68,0:25:33.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウィリアム・ティンダルはブリュッセルの北にある\Nビルボールデで投獄されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.95,0:25:36.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,１年以上 獄中で過ごしている間—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.75,0:25:40.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,残酷な死が待ち受けていることを\N予期していたことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.69,0:25:44.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,ティンダルは\N英語に影響を与えた人として有名です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.86,0:25:49.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 彼の働きは\N学問的な志だけによるのではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.86,0:25:52.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ティンダルは聖書を愛していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.70,0:25:56.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉について述べた詩編作者と\N同じ気持ちだったと言えるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.97,0:26:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしはどんなにあなたの律法を\N 愛していることでしょう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.31,0:26:06.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,激しい迫害にもかかわらず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.65,0:26:10.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書とその知恵は\N今日まで生き残っており—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.15,0:26:14.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,著者の言葉を忠実に伝えているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.32,0:26:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの人が聖書を大切にしてきたのも\N不思議ではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.20,0:26:31.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,嬉しいことに このドキュメンタリーの\N長編版が今月中に公開されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.71,0:26:38.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,命をかけて神の言葉を広めた\Nほかの人たちの例も収められています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.41,0:26:42.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,“聖書を大切にした人たち”\N と題するビデオで— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.02,0:26:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオ・オンデマンドの\N“聖書”の見出しに掲載されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.19,0:26:53.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがみ言葉を保存し 広めることに\N直接関わっておられることを知ると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.46,0:26:59.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書こそ 神に近づく\N唯一の正しい方法であると確信できます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.83,0:27:02.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,英国出身のデービッド・シブレーは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.60,0:27:08.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,子どもの頃 聖書を読んだことがなく\N人間の伝統を教えられていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.44,0:27:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が真理を理解する\N助けになったでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.38,0:27:21.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは1930年に生まれ\Nリトルハンプトンで暮らしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.32,0:27:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,海のそばで\N気持ちの良い静かな場所です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.30,0:27:30.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,よく 歩いて田舎の方に行きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.73,0:27:35.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,何かを読むより\N自然を見るほうが好きなんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.54,0:27:39.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,1939年 戦争が始まりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.87,0:27:45.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしの町も巻き込まれ\N戦闘機が飛び交うようになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.58,0:27:48.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある年下の男の子がいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.55,0:27:53.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,日曜日の朝 空爆があって\Nその子の家は破壊され—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.36,0:27:56.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,その子も亡くなったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.59,0:28:01.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,母に聞いた覚えがあります\N“どうして死んじゃったの？” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.36,0:28:07.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,母は “天国で神様と一緒になったのよ”\Nと言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.17,0:28:13.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 意味が分かりません\Nその子を死ぬようにしたのが神様だなんて\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.71,0:28:18.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだとしたら 戦争も神様のせいです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.81,0:28:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,気は晴れませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.42,0:28:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも そう考えることにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.29,0:28:29.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,宗教は まあ良いものだろうけど—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.02,0:28:33.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,していることと一致していない\Nと思っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.13,0:28:38.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,どこかずれていて自分のために\Nなるとも思えませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.60,0:28:42.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,賛美歌の本や祈祷書は\N教会に持っていくのに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.44,0:28:46.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書はただ自分で\N持っているだけなんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.37,0:28:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人と研究して\N初めて聖書を開きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.48,0:28:58.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,17歳か18歳の時\Nジョー・グラッドウィン兄弟が来てくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.79,0:29:02.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは聖書を全く知らなかったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.39,0:29:07.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,反論するつもりはなかったんですが\N兄弟は聖書にこうある と言うけど—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.50,0:29:11.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの人たちの考えも\N確かめようと思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.77,0:29:18.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして やっぱり兄弟の言うとおりで\N聖書が正しいと分かったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.64,0:29:22.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,今まで知らなかったことを\N聖書から学びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.84,0:29:28.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまで長きにわたって\N様々な翻訳の聖書を集めてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.25,0:29:30.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,いろいろな翻訳を読むと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.05,0:29:34.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉は変わっていない\Nということが分かります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.86,0:29:39.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,1950年\N20歳でバプテスマを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.49,0:29:44.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず 正規開拓奉仕を始め \Nそして ベテルに来ました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.50,0:29:49.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 ベテルを出て\N巡回 地域の奉仕をし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.34,0:29:53.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,今は ベテルの執筆デスクで\N奉仕しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.34,0:29:57.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,受けた割り当てを通して\N確信を強められてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.75,0:30:01.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが指示を与えておられ\N聖霊の助けがあれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.68,0:30:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが願っておられることを\N何でも行なえます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.32,0:30:07.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,それだけでなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.82,0:30:12.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,この組織は統治体の指導のもとに\N成長を続けてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.96,0:30:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,このような組織はほかにありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.06,0:30:20.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,この組織にとどまり続けるべきなんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.87,0:30:24.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,人生にかかわる疑問の答えを\Nいろいろ探しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.71,0:30:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 聖書だけが答えてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.68,0:30:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがずっと教えてくださっている\Nことに感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.02,0:30:43.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,シブレー兄弟の\N聖書への感謝に心を打たれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.22,0:30:48.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉への感謝を表す方法を\N覚えていますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.46,0:30:53.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,読み 研究し 収められている\N深い考えを黙想し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.80,0:30:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 聖霊を受けて書かれた教えを\N生活に当てはめることによってです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.01,0:31:03.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするとき\N聖霊が自分の内面に影響を与え—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.91,0:31:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,願いや人生の目的を形作ってくれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.25,0:31:14.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 仲間の人間に対して\N長年憤りを抱き—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.66,0:31:18.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,殺したいと思うほどなら\Nどうでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.53,0:31:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような深刻な状況で\N神の言葉は何ができるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.33,0:31:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘブライ 4章12節を思い出して下さい\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.60,0:31:33.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,“神の言葉は生きていて 力を及ぼし—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.04,0:31:38.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,“心の考えと意向とを\N 見分けることができるのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.11,0:31:40.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです エホバは聖書を保存し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.98,0:31:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉の力を実感できる\Nようにしてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.39,0:31:50.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロシアのウラジミール・オリホフと\Nヴァレリー・サポロジスキーは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.99,0:31:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,憎み合う敵同士でしたが\Nその力をじかに経験しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.44,0:32:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはギャングのリーダーでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.28,0:32:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,人から金を奪い取り 誘拐して脅し\N放り出しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.56,0:32:26.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな言いなりになり\Nわたしを恐れていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.79,0:32:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,快感でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.67,0:32:34.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,歯向かう人間は\N決して許しませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.07,0:32:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,こう言いました—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.00,0:32:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“石を投げつけてみろ！\N お前を山に埋めてやる！”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.31,0:32:47.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,1993年 警官として—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.72,0:32:50.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギャングとリーダーである\Nウラジミールの情報収集に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.85,0:32:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,割り当てられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.89,0:32:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある時 警官が\Nわたしを捕まえに来ました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.00,0:33:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,奴らに復しゅうしてやる と誓いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.68,0:33:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,尋問中 ウラジミールをけなし\N打ちのめしてやろうとしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.85,0:33:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,お互いに憎んでいたんです！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.76,0:33:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヴァレリーに言いました—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.73,0:33:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“覚えていろ！\N 牢屋から出たらお前を殺してやる！”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.27,0:33:42.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,手始めに 奴の車を爆破し\Nそれでもだめなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.14,0:33:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,殺してやろう と考えていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.24,0:33:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼の脅しが本気だったので\N命の危険を感じました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.31,0:33:56.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲間に頼んで彼の監視を強化し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.75,0:34:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,決して脱獄しないようにさせました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.06,0:34:09.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ監房に入っていた一人が\N新約聖書を持っていたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.60,0:34:11.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んでいいか尋ねました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.90,0:34:16.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,関心があるのを知ってか\N誰かが“ものみの塔”誌をくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.90,0:34:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,読むにつれて 自分とは違う\N本当の人たちがいることが分かりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.51,0:34:28.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,全く違う生き方\N将来の希望を持っている人たちです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.45,0:34:30.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,衝撃でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.52,0:34:34.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,牢屋の周りで\N他の5冊の雑誌を見つけました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.62,0:34:36.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,読みふけりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.42,0:34:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理を見つけたと強く確信しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.26,0:34:47.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻との面会が初めて許された時\N“真理を見つけたぞ！” と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.50,0:34:52.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻は急速に進歩し\N2年後にバプテスマを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.54,0:34:54.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻の支えは貴重でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.81,0:35:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎回訪ね 正直に そして\N神に忠実であるよう力づけてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.12,0:35:08.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,1993年に証人が訪ねてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.32,0:35:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書研究には同意しましたが\N心には響きませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.23,0:35:16.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある時 集まりに誘われ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.53,0:35:18.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウラジミールが\Nエホバの証人になるために—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.87,0:35:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマを受けようとしていると\N知らされました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.14,0:35:26.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの犯罪者がです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.34,0:35:28.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ショックでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.04,0:35:31.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,家に帰って泣き崩れました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.58,0:35:34.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的に進歩しなければと感じました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.82,0:35:38.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼にできるのなら\Nわたしにもできるはずだからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.75,0:35:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,人生で初めて祈ったのは\Nまさにその時でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.26,0:35:48.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,1997年10月に釈放されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.06,0:35:52.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,釈放後 兄弟たちは\Nある集まりを設けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.70,0:35:56.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちは\Nその集まりに招待してくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.37,0:36:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,着いてみると わたしがかつて\N家宅捜査をした場所だと気づいたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.04,0:36:05.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヴァレリーが部屋に入ってくると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.71,0:36:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは抱き合って\N声をあげて泣きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.29,0:36:15.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼の目は 以前とは\Nまったく違っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.89,0:36:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,優しい目でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.09,0:36:23.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,胸から重荷が\N取り除かれた感じがしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.93,0:36:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“兄弟！” お互いに許しを求めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.14,0:36:34.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,1997年11月23日—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.11,0:36:36.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,バプテスマを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.74,0:36:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じプールで ヴァレリーと！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.78,0:36:45.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは真の友となりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.75,0:36:49.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では同じ会衆で二人とも長老です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.59,0:36:51.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻とわたしはよく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.36,0:36:55.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし聖書を勉強していなかったら\Nどうなっていただろうと話します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.80,0:36:59.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,多分 今頃は生きていなかったでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.17,0:37:01.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,今でも家族と一緒です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.47,0:37:06.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,更に 霊的な家族を\Nクリスチャン会衆内に持っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.11,0:37:10.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,かつての敵は\N今では兄弟であり親友です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.24,0:37:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,大切なこととして\Nエホバとの良い関係を持っているんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.08,0:37:19.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,神だけが\N彼のような根っからの犯罪者や—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.99,0:37:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしのような者をも\N変化させることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.16,0:37:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは分裂が永遠になくなることを\N心から願っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.91,0:37:44.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが ご自分の言葉が消されない\Nようにされた理由に気づきましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.41,0:37:45.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を読むことが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.85,0:37:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれほどわたしたちのためになるか\Nご存じなのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.25,0:37:54.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのメッセージは非常に強力なので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.22,0:38:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウラジミールとヴァレリーは\N生き方を変え 親友にまでなりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.33,0:38:04.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書翻訳に携わる人はごく少数ですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.67,0:38:08.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは皆 \N近所の人に聖書を分かち—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.37,0:38:13.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバについての正確な知識を\N得るよう助けることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.41,0:38:17.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のドラマで\N家族が楽しんでいる神権的活動と—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.78,0:38:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,熱意を持てるよう何を行なう必要が\Nあったかに注目してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.42,0:38:57.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと待った\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.15,0:39:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは このストーリーの結末部分です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.66,0:39:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも大切なのは どうやって\Nここまで来ることができたのか です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.77,0:39:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族の宣教に援助が必要だとは\N思ってもみませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.11,0:39:29.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻も娘も 開拓者だし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.72,0:39:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,息子も ちゃんとした伝道者\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.22,0:39:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしも まだ開拓はできないけど\N家族のためになんでもやってきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.50,0:39:48.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,できるだけ一緒に奉仕に出る事が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.14,0:39:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族のためにできる最善の事だと\N思い込んでいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.58,0:39:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも もっと必要なことがあると\N気づかされたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.78,0:40:04.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここ数週間 野外奉仕の群れの監督は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.32,0:40:08.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたち家族と一緒に奉仕するよう\N真剣に努力してくれて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.86,0:40:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いくつかの課題に\N親切に気づかせてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.46,0:40:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕時間はよく入っているけど\N再訪問が少しずつ減っていること—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.10,0:40:26.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,子どもとの研究以外 家族のだれも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.27,0:40:30.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,研究司会をしていないことに\N注意を向けてくれたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.51,0:40:34.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは宣教の質を\N改善するために何ができるか— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.75,0:40:37.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟に尋ねてみました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.59,0:40:43.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟はローマ 15章19節の\Nパウロの言葉を見せてくれました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.26,0:40:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしは キリストについての\N 良いたよりを徹底的に宣べ伝えました”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.13,0:40:54.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから 次の家族の崇拝で\Nパウロの宣教を研究して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.30,0:40:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その模範から学ぶのはどうか\Nと勧めてくれたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.25,0:41:13.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロの宣教を調べるにつれて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.05,0:41:16.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,産出的な奉仕に必要なものが\N分かりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.86,0:41:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,大胆さです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.49,0:41:22.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェソス 6章19節には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.13,0:41:25.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そして わたしのためにも祈ってください”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.50,0:41:29.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしが口を開くときに\N 話す能力を与えられ—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.04,0:41:31.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,“はばかりのないことばで\N 良いたよりの神聖な奥義を—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.97,0:41:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“知らせることができるように\N するためです”とあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.28,0:41:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,娘の璃菜は パウロが説得力ある仕方で\N人々と論じ合ったことに注目しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.43,0:41:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻の恵子は 相手との共通の土台を\N築く仕方に注目しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.43,0:42:02.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは 会話を\Nエホバの方に導くために—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.94,0:42:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,知られていない異教の神の祭壇さえ\N使ったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.08,0:42:14.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして春斗は テモテ第二でパウロが\N“恥ずべきところのない働き人として”—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.58,0:42:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“真理の言葉を正しく”用いた点に\N 注目しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.35,0:42:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは宣教で聖句を使うのが\N巧みだったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.06,0:42:31.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,もうお分かりでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.90,0:42:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これが このストーリーの結末\Nだったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.81,0:42:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは補助開拓奉仕を始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.05,0:43:01.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では 家族でたくさんの再訪問を行ない\N進歩的な研究生も何件か見つけました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.73,0:43:05.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも どうやってここまで\N来たのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.87,0:43:08.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族でパウロから学びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.77,0:43:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その模範と彼がどのように\N徹底的に証ししたかをね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.95,0:43:24.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,群れの監督は \N家族の宣教の改善に必要なことを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.99,0:43:27.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,単に列挙することもできました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.55,0:43:33.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 聖書中の特定の原則に\N父親の注意を向けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.39,0:43:39.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,結局 神の言葉だけが\N教えるために“霊感を受け”ています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.77,0:43:42.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,一般の言語に翻訳された聖書は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.34,0:43:45.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,1500年代にヨーロッパ中に\N広まり始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.91,0:43:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし さらに遠くの場所では\Nもっと長い時間がかかりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.11,0:43:55.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,1766年に グリーンランド語の\Nギリシャ語聖書—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.38,0:44:00.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるいは新約聖書全体が\N初めて出版されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.09,0:44:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,現在 約5万人が\Nグリーンランド語を話します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.49,0:44:09.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,昨年8月 わたしは\Nスカンディナビア支部が監督する—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.70,0:44:13.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,グリーンランドでの\N地区大会に出席しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.70,0:44:17.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,グリーンランドは\Nわたしが11年間 開拓奉仕をした—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.57,0:44:20.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニューファンドランドの北にあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.07,0:44:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで そこに行って兄弟たちに\N会えたのは素晴らしい経験でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.25,0:44:31.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,スカンディナビア各地から\N約400人の兄弟姉妹が自費で旅行し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.29,0:44:34.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,グリーンランドでの大会を支えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.89,0:44:38.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,グリーンランドは広大な氷で\N覆われていますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.56,0:44:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理を慕う温かい心を\N持つ人たちが大勢います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.58,0:44:58.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの述べた\N“地の最も遠い所”とは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.01,0:45:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,グリーンランドなのかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.42,0:45:04.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,アーネ・マトソンです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.45,0:45:09.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,妻のカリンと34年以上\Nグリーンランドで暮らしています \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.69,0:45:12.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,国中を旅行して 神の王国を宣べ伝え—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.79,0:45:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい経験をしてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.76,0:45:18.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,グリーンランドの最初の伝道者は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.87,0:45:23.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,1950年代に来た\N二人の特別開拓者です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.17,0:45:25.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,船による伝道旅行の持ち物は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.54,0:45:28.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,テントと簡単な装備だけでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.68,0:45:30.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,耐えなければならなかったのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.48,0:45:34.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,厳しい寒さ\N地元の僧職者の反対—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.35,0:45:37.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 食べ物を狙う そり犬\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.25,0:45:39.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし その働きは 国内における—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.42,0:45:44.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,後の宣教活動の基礎を\N据えるものとなりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.46,0:45:46.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,60年代と70年代に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.86,0:45:51.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,デンマークからの多くの家族が\N宣教のために引っ越して来ました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.67,0:45:54.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしが10代だった 1971年に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.90,0:45:58.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしの家族も\Nデンマークから移り住みました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.81,0:46:03.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,難しい地元の言語を\N兄弟姉妹は一生懸命に学び—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.01,0:46:07.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,それが 区域の人々の\N良い反応につながりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.82,0:46:13.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,1973年には グリーンランド語の\N「ものみの塔」誌が発行され始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.65,0:46:19.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ナパスリアク・アラペルナールシフィク」\N と発音するのも ひと苦労です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.29,0:46:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,とはいえ 発行以来\Nグリーンランドでは評判の雑誌です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.13,0:46:28.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,以前 入植地に住むご夫婦に\Nお会いしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.30,0:46:32.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,お二人は長年「ものみの塔」誌を\N受け取っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.37,0:46:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,憂うつな気分で\N朝目ざめることの多いお二人は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.55,0:46:40.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,雑誌を読むと気分が良くなるので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.95,0:46:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ部分を 何度も何度も\N読んだとのことでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.63,0:46:54.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,寒くなって 雪が降ると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.46,0:46:58.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,半年間も一面が\N雪のじゅうたんで覆われるので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.13,0:47:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,伝道者にとって夏は働き時です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.90,0:47:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,証言をあまり受けることのない\N町や入植地があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.74,0:47:12.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,町を結ぶ道路はないので\N遠隔地にはボートで行き—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.68,0:47:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,関心を示した人とは\N電話で連絡を取り合います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.89,0:47:21.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,「わたしの聖書物語」の本は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.99,0:47:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書に深い敬意を抱く\N本当に多くの家庭に配布されてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.80,0:47:33.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,24年にわたり わたしたちが\N宣教のためにボートで移動した距離は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.27,0:47:35.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,なんと地球2周分です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.57,0:47:38.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,苦労しましたし お金もかかりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.87,0:47:40.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバの祝福により—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.67,0:47:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この遠い地で 何年にもわたり\N宣教を続けることができました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.19,0:47:55.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここでの宣教活動は\N素晴らしい経験になります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.79,0:47:59.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々はよく耳を傾けてくれて親切です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.69,0:48:03.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでも 地元の方が\N初めてバプテスマを受けたのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.43,0:48:07.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,熱心な奉仕が行われた\N18年後のことでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.83,0:48:13.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では 5つの会衆に所属する\N150人以上の伝道者が奉仕しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.34,0:48:15.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,60年以上にわたり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.08,0:48:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはこの地の活動を\N確かに祝福してくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.32,0:48:35.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,2016年8月 主都のヌークで\N文字通り特別な大会が開かれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.26,0:48:37.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,スカンディナビアの兄弟姉妹が来て—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.50,0:48:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの大会に出席してくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.27,0:48:50.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰を強める話をしてくださった\Nマーク・サンダーソン兄弟の訪問に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.81,0:48:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは大いに力づけられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.35,0:49:01.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理を理解できるというのは\N素晴らしいことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.09,0:49:03.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分のような取るに足りない人間に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.39,0:49:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが注意を向けてくださる\Nというのは 本当に驚きです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.90,0:49:14.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,その特異な教えと原則に\N従って初めて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.64,0:49:19.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書が自分の生活の質を\N向上させるということを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.04,0:49:23.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,はっきり理解できました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.41,0:49:27.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界の他の土地から\N遠く離れたわたしたちですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.11,0:49:28.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,今回の大会で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.58,0:49:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中の兄弟たちが\Nぐっと身近になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.59,0:49:46.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,大会の最高出席者数は614人で\Nグリーンランドの最高数でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.90,0:49:50.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,スカンディナビアの他の場所から\N出席した兄弟たちも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.64,0:49:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,関心ある人たちを招待する\Nキャンペーンに参加しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.14,0:49:59.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,たった2時間で\N主都ヌークが網羅されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.61,0:50:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい証言でした！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.82,0:50:07.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,“地の最も遠い所にまで”\N 証言することに関連して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.72,0:50:11.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体のジェフリー･ジャクソン兄弟が\N最近の朝の崇拝で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.93,0:50:18.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,19世紀に聖書が数多くの言語に\Nどのように翻訳されたかを説明しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.93,0:50:22.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,“「最も遠い所にまで」達する“\N という題で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.44,0:50:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオ・オンデマンドで\N今 見ることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.68,0:50:35.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月後半 2011年の年次総会の\N素敵なビデオが掲載されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.98,0:50:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,夫が統治体の成員だったやもめの姉妹たち\N5人へのインタビューです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.36,0:50:44.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理を知ったいきさつや—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.26,0:50:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年の忠実な奉仕の\N楽しい思い出が話されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.16,0:50:55.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,“夫が統治体の成員だった忠実な\N 姉妹たちへのインタビュー”と題し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.27,0:50:57.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオ・オンデマンドの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.10,0:51:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“経験とインタビュー“の\N カテゴリーに掲載されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.01,0:51:05.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは ご自分の言葉を通して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.68,0:51:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最高のプレゼントを\N与えてくださったと思いませんか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.22,0:51:12.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,プレゼントを\N与えてくださっただけでなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.92,0:51:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何度も何度も わたしたちのために\N保存されるようにしてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.53,0:51:23.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のプログラムにあったように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.06,0:51:26.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,デービッド・シブレー \Nウラジミール・オリホフ —\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.80,0:51:30.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヴァレリー・サポロジスキー\Nといった兄弟たちは皆— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.30,0:51:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の言葉の力と導きを経験しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.38,0:51:41.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒パウロの模範に倣って\N宣教を改善した家族から—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.65,0:51:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書が“教え 物事を正すのに有益”\Nであることも分かりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.06,0:51:58.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです 神の言葉はこれまで存続し\Nこれからも永久に存続します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.23,0:52:02.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご存じのとおり 2017年4月3日—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.27,0:52:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウォーウィックにある\Nミュージアムが一般公開されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.41,0:52:12.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,“聖書と神のみ名”と題する\N 拡張された展示に加え—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.38,0:52:19.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,“神の言葉は永久に存続する”\N と題する新しい展示もあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.39,0:52:21.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうぞ 見に来てください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.99,0:52:25.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,今回のブロードキャスティングで\N扱われた点を例示する—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.33,0:52:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい聖書のコレクションを見て\Nわくわくすることでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.26,0:52:34.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編作者は霊感のもとに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.10,0:52:39.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしはどんなにあなたの律法を\N 愛していることでしょう“と書きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.17,0:52:43.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちも エホバを愛し\N聖書を愛しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.41,0:52:48.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,幾世紀もの間 神の言葉を\N保存するために用いられた人々を含め—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.62,0:52:51.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に大勢の人々も愛してきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.89,0:52:55.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,これを思いにとめ\N今月のミュージックビデオ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.29,0:53:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたのことば 永遠に”\N を楽しみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.35,0:53:24.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,時を 越えて\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.45,0:53:29.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,明かされてきた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.42,0:53:34.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの愛が\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.59,0:53:40.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうして 今 ここに\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.03,0:53:44.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,その名 示し\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.84,0:53:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,希望を灯す\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.88,0:53:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,輝き 失せず\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.95,0:54:00.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,尚も 道 照らして\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.25,0:54:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,誓いを 胸に\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.16,0:54:10.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,志 果たし\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.56,0:54:15.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,一言も 失わず\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.17,0:54:20.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ声 聴いてる\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.84,0:54:25.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの言葉\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.58,0:54:31.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,海より 深く\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.02,0:54:36.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,風のように 心そよぎ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.16,0:54:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,続く 陽のように\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.80,0:54:48.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵の炎も\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.87,0:54:53.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,決して 奪えない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.81,0:54:58.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,誇らしく 守り抜く\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.65,0:55:03.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,変わらぬ愛がある\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.85,0:55:08.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,企みに行く手を\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.99,0:55:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,封じられようと\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.16,0:55:19.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,命さえも 惜しくはない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.23,0:55:24.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,沈黙などしない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.70,0:55:29.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの その言葉\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.51,0:55:34.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,海より深く\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.65,0:55:39.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,風のように 心そよぎ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.92,0:55:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,続く陽のように\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.13,0:55:49.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの名は エホバ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.96,0:55:54.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠<とわ>に 美しい\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.97,0:56:00.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,湧き上がる 賛美歌う\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.51,0:56:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,命の日の限り\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.41,0:56:13.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,決して 色褪せない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.12,0:56:18.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの言葉\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.09,0:56:23.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,青草 枯れ 花 落ちても\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.56,0:56:30.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,続く 永遠に\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.54,0:56:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠に\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.19,0:56:49.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に美しい歌です！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.46,0:56:54.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリの兄弟姉妹からのあいさつで\N今月のプログラムを閉じましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.83,0:57:00.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリは西アフリカに位置し\Nサハラ砂漠の奥深くにまで及んでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.93,0:57:04.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,国の北側は暑く\N砂に覆われていますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.90,0:57:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,南側はニジェール川で潤い\N森林や植物で緑豊かです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.18,0:57:16.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,この国の証人たちには\N膨大な仕事があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.45,0:57:23.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,人口に対するエホバの証人の比率は\Nおよそ5万9千人に1人です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.12,0:57:26.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,加えて 途方もない距離があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.63,0:57:29.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,およそ300人の伝道者が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.13,0:57:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,フランスの2倍以上の広さを持つ\N地域を網羅しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.07,0:57:37.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリは世界でも特に暑い国です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.67,0:57:44.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのため 外の涼しい木陰で\N集会を開く群れや会衆もあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.11,0:57:46.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,公用語はフランス語ですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.18,0:57:51.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,たいていの人は地元の言語である\Nバンバラ語のほうがよく理解できます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.48,0:57:57.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで ほとんどの集会はバンバラ語で\N開かれるか通訳されています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.06,0:58:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最近 別の地元の言語\Nボム語の言語クラスが開かれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.10,0:58:07.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに アメリカ手話の\N群れの7人の伝道者が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.70,0:58:14.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリに住む35万人以上の聴覚障害者に\N証言するよう割り当てられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.91,0:58:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,昨年の記念式の出席者は\N合計1100人以上でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.45,0:58:24.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,招待状を受け取ったある男性は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.22,0:58:31.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,足が不自由であるにもかかわらず\N記念式に出席するため3キロ歩きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.12,0:58:36.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では定期的に集会に出席し\N良い進歩を遂げています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.60,0:58:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最近 首都に新しい\N王国会館が建てられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.10,0:58:46.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,市や州の当局者 近所の人\Nまた たくさんの通行人は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.27,0:58:51.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,見たことに感銘を受け\Nここで働く兄弟たちを褒めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.38,0:58:55.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリの兄弟姉妹たちが愛を送っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.48,0:58:58.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちも皆さんを愛しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.79,0:59:11.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の世界本部から\NJW Broadcastingでした\N
